dSocial or Service Providers maintain facilities and the use and disclosure of information about you as described in this Privacy Policy.</li><li>We use commercially reasonable safeguards to help keep the information collected through the Service secure and take reasonable steps (such as requesting a unique password) to verify your identity before granting you access to your account. However, PaidSocial cannot ensure the security of any information you transmit to PaidSocial or guarantee that information on the Service may not be accessed, disclosed, altered, or destroyed. In the event that any personal information in our possession or under our control is compromised as a result of a security breach, we will take reasonable steps to investigate the situation and, where appropriate, notify those individuals whose information may have been compromised and take other steps in accordance with applicable laws or regulations.</li><li>Some of the examples of the data security controls in place at PaidSocial (this is not an exhaustive list):<ol><li>The use of encryption when personal data is transferred to PaidSocial’s servers;</li><li>Limited access to personal data by PaidSocial staff on a need-to-know basis and the use of robust authentication processes;</li><li>The use of data centers with effective physical and logical data security controls, and the use of reputable third parties who have demonstrated security consciousness; and</li><li>Secure office premises and staff that are aware of their data protection responsibilities.</li></ol></li><li>You are responsible for maintaining the secrecy of your unique password and account information, and for controlling access to emails between you and PaidSocial, at all times.</li></ol><h3>Your Choices About Your Information:</h3><ol start="22"><li>We strive to provide you with choices regarding the personal information you provide to us. This section describes mechanisms we provide for you to control certain uses and disclosures of over your information.</li><li>You have the following rights, which you can request from PaidSocial at any time:<ol><li>To stop processing your personal information on a temporary basis;</li><li>The right to be forgotten (deleted from our servers);</li><li>The right to object to processing; and</li><li>The right to access, change, or correct your personal information.</li></ol></li><li>Email melissa@PaidSocial should you wish to exercise any of the rights above.</li><li>Following termination or deactivation of your account, PaidSocial or its Service Providers may retain information (including your profile information) and your Content for a commercially reasonable time for backup, archival, and/or audit purposes.  Unless you contact us to delete your personal information, PaidSocial will only retain your personal information for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy, but in no event longer than 6 months, unless a longer retention period is required by law.</li></ol><h3>Children’s Privacy:</h3><ol start="26"><li>PaidSocial does not knowingly collect or solicit any information from anyone under the age of 18 or knowingly allow such persons to register for the Service. The Service and its content are not directed at anyone under the age of 18. In the event that we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under age 18 without parental consent, we will delete that information as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any information from or about a child under 18, please contact us at melissa@PaidSocial.</li></ol><h3>Other Websites and Services:</h3><ol start="27"><li>We are not responsible for the practices employed by any websites or services linked to or from our Service, including the information or content contained within them. Please remember that when you use a link to go from our Service to another website or service, our Privacy Policy does not apply to those third-party websites or services. Your browsing and interaction on any third-party website or service, including those that have a link on our website, are subject to that third party's own rules and policies. In addition, you agree that we are not responsible and do not have control over any third-parties that you authorize to access your Content. If you are using a third-party website or service and you allow them to access your Content, you do so at your own risk.</li></ol><h3>The Existence of Automated Decision-Making, Including Profiling:</h3><ol start="28"><li>PaidSocial does not take any decisions involving the use of algorithms or profiling that significantly affects you.</li></ol><h3>How to Contact PaidSocial:</h3><ol start="29"><li>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or the Service, please contact our Data Privacy Officer at melissa@PaidSocial. EU residents may also exercise their data subject rights by contacting our Data Privacy Officer.</li><li>If you are unsatisfied with the reply you receive from PaidSocial, you may refer your complaint to the relevant regulator in your jurisdiction.  If you ask us, we will endeavor to provide you with information about relevant complaint avenues which may be applicable to your circumstances.</li></ol><h3>Changes to Our Privacy Policy:</h3><ol start="31"><li>PaidSocial may modify or update this Privacy Policy from time to time, so please review it periodically. We may provide you additional forms of notice of modifications or updates as appropriate under the circumstances. Your continued use of PaidSocial or the Service after any modification to this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such modification.</li><li>If at any time in the future we plan to share personal information with more third parties, PaidSocial will maintain GDPR compliance and a high standard of care for your personal information.</li></ol><h3>Additional Privacy Information for Residents of the European Economic Area:</h3><ol start="33"><li>PaidSocial has taken important steps for compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation 2018 (GDPR) for EU users.  As a data controller, PaidSocial understands our obligations under the GDPR (EU) 2016/679 and has taken the following steps:<ol><li>Revised this Privacy Policy to provide you with a clear understanding of our privacy practices;</li><li>Appointed a PaidSocial Data Protection Officer who can respond to EU data subjects and Data Protection Authorities as needed;</li><li>Introduced new product features and functionality to allow users better control over their privacy;</li><li>Reviewed our data inventory and third party relationships to gain a complete picture of data flows and take a Privacy by Design approach to our data holdings;</li><li>Enhanced our data security controls such that regardless of the data flow, reasonable efforts are made to protect our user data at all times;</li><li>Developed a procedure to respond to any requests that may be received from users who are EU residents regarding their data subject rights;</li><li>Reviewed and revised our data retention rules to ensure PaidSocial is not retaining personal information that is no longer in use;</li><li>Required our third parties who we entrust with PaidSocial user data to commit to the continued protection of such data and comply with the GDPR responsibilities as a data processor; and</li><li>Instituted a privacy data breach response plan to ensure any privacy incidents are handled effectively and efficiently.</li></ol></li><li>Controller: PaidSocial is a private company, established in the U.S.A.  Our address is 8 The Greet Suite A, Dover, DE 19901 and our contact email address is melissa@PaidSocial.  For the purposes of the GDPR, we are the data controller.</li>
      <li>Legal Basis: We describe in the section above “How we use your information” the purposes for which we use the data collected and shared.  Where we are using the data in order to provide PaidSocial’s services to you, our legal basis for such use is on the basis of our contract with you.  For all other purposes, our legal basis is our legitimate interest in running our business; including ensuring PaidSocial’s Service functions properly and improving and creating new products and services except where we obtain your consent for a particular processing, in which event the legal basis will be your consent.</li><li>Your Rights: To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at melissa@PaidSocial.  Please note that these rights are limited, for example, where fulfilling your request would adversely affect other individuals or where we are required by law to retain your personal data.<ol start="10"><li>Access and portability: You are entitled to request access to your personal information we hold and be provided with certain information about how we use your personal information and who we share it with. Where you have provided your personal data to us with your consent, you have the right to ask us for a copy of this data in a structured, machine readable format and to ask us to share (port) this data to another data controller.</li><li>Correction: You have the right to ask us to correct your personal data where it is inaccurate or incomplete.</li><li>Right to deletion: In certain circumstances, you have the right to ask us to delete the personal data we hold about you.</li><li>Restriction: In certain circumstances, you have the right to ask us to restrict (stop any active) processing of your personal data.</li><li>Objection: You can object to our processing of your personal data based on our legitimate interests and we will no longer process your personal data unless we can demonstrate an overriding legitimate ground.</li><li>Withdrawal of consent: In the event we have relied upon your consent to process your personal data, you may withdraw consent at any time by contacting us at melissa@PaidSocial.</li><li>Cease use: Finally, you may always cease using PaidSocial’s Service, and you may deactivate your account.  After a reasonable time following such deactivation, as set forth above, PaidSocial would no longer have access to your personal information.</li><li>Complaints: In the event that you wish to make a complaint about how we process your personal data, please contact us in the first instance at melissa@PaidSocial and we will endeavor to deal with your request as soon as possible. This is without prejudice to your right to raise a complaint with a relevant supervisory authority.</li></ol></li></ol></div><div class="_1abRA"><a class="_16kVD" href="/2257-compliance"></a></div>
